721
00:45:09,039 --> 00:45:14,911
[ Sobbing ]
But the closer that we got...
the worse I treated him.

722
00:45:18,649 --> 00:45:20,950
And I don't know why.
[ Sniffles ]

723
00:45:23,554 --> 00:45:26,689
I just
couldn't stop myself.

724
00:45:27,825 --> 00:45:29,559
<i>[ Thunder Rumbling ]</i>

725
00:45:29,561 --> 00:45:34,597
No matter
how shitty I was...

726
00:45:36,233 --> 00:45:38,234
he would take it.

727
00:45:43,741 --> 00:45:45,308
And...

728
00:45:48,011 --> 00:45:51,948
he told me he loved me.

729
00:45:57,821 --> 00:45:59,856
And I laughed at him.

730
00:46:03,460 --> 00:46:09,065
[ Inhales ]
I wish that I could
take it back.

731
00:46:11,802 --> 00:46:13,903
I tried.

732
00:46:16,473 --> 00:46:19,342
But when I saw him
at school,
he just avoided me.

733
00:46:22,780 --> 00:46:26,549
He was angry all the time.

734
00:46:31,121 --> 00:46:33,456
I didn't even know
who he was anymore.

735
00:46:36,393 --> 00:46:38,461
[ Kim ]
Now you know.

736
00:46:40,130 --> 00:46:42,131
You're lucky
to be rid of him.

737
00:46:44,001 --> 00:46:46,903
Fuck you!

738
00:46:46,905 --> 00:46:47,970
Fucking bitch!

739
00:46:48,939 --> 00:46:51,274
He'd be alive
if it weren't for you.

740
00:46:51,276 --> 00:46:53,576
He'd still be alive
if you hadn't stabbed him!

741
00:46:53,578 --> 00:46:55,011
- We're goin' to jail.
- Shut up!

742
00:46:55,013 --> 00:46:58,581
Stop it!
We are all going to jail.
You know that, right?

743
00:46:58,583 --> 00:47:01,117
- All of us!
- No, we're not.

744
00:47:01,119 --> 00:47:03,452
I am scared,
but I'm not stupid.

745
00:47:03,454 --> 00:47:05,421
[ Sobbing ]
It's not gonna be okay.

746
00:47:05,423 --> 00:47:09,325
Nothing ever is
going to be okay
ever again.

747
00:47:09,327 --> 00:47:12,495
And you can't fix that!
Don't you understand that?

748
00:47:12,497 --> 00:47:15,198
[ Dwayne ]
Just stop it,
all of you.

749
00:47:15,200 --> 00:47:19,335
Cryin' and arguin' about
who's to blame is not gonna
change anything that happened.

750
00:47:20,470 --> 00:47:22,171
You asked me
why I came back?

751
00:47:26,643 --> 00:47:28,811
Because we're all to blame.

752
00:47:28,813 --> 00:47:30,012
[ Gasps ]

753
00:47:32,583 --> 00:47:35,451
That's God's simple truth.
The boy is dead.

754
00:47:35,453 --> 00:47:39,355
I'm about saving my ass,
and that means yours too.

755
00:47:39,357 --> 00:47:42,258
[ Gasps ]
What are we gonna do, man?

756
00:47:42,260 --> 00:47:45,461
<i>We</i> are going in there
and gettin' rid of him,

757
00:47:45,463 --> 00:47:47,029
then gettin'
the hell outta here.

758
00:47:47,031 --> 00:47:48,965
Nobody here knows nothin'
about that kid.

759
00:47:48,967 --> 00:47:52,001
He was at the party,
and nobody's seen him.

760
00:47:52,003 --> 00:47:53,936
You got it?

761
00:47:53,938 --> 00:47:58,975
Then, we take him north.
They'll never find him.

762
00:48:00,844 --> 00:48:02,245
Yo, come on. Let's go.
Let's go!

763
00:48:02,247 --> 00:48:06,048
Is this what
we should be doing?
This isn't right.

764
00:48:06,050 --> 00:48:08,551
Anybody have a better idea?

765
00:48:11,922 --> 00:48:13,222
<i>[ Thunder Rumbling ]</i>

766
00:48:13,224 --> 00:48:17,026
Like it or not,
we're all complicit.

767
00:48:18,428 --> 00:48:20,596
You want to survive this?

768
00:48:37,247 --> 00:48:38,347
Fuck.

769
00:48:38,349 --> 00:48:39,916
[ Gasping ]
- Not those.

770
00:48:47,758 --> 00:48:49,358
Yo, Shannon, hurry up
with those towels.

771
00:48:49,360 --> 00:48:51,761
- Use these.
- [ Breathing Heavily ]

772
00:48:51,763 --> 00:48:53,696
We'll get through this.

773
00:48:53,698 --> 00:48:55,398
We have to.

774
00:48:55,400 --> 00:48:56,666
Where do you want this?

775
00:48:56,668 --> 00:48:59,268
Hold on. We got to
get this cleaned up first.

776
00:49:01,305 --> 00:49:03,205
Hey, Shannon,
where's the garbage bags?

777
00:49:03,207 --> 00:49:04,774
Over there.

778
00:49:05,509 --> 00:49:07,443
[ Glasses Clattering ]

779
00:49:13,083 --> 00:49:13,649
[ Bag Snaps ]

780
00:49:17,921 --> 00:49:22,091
Mica, give us a hand.
You two get that party mess
cleaned up.

781
00:49:25,862 --> 00:49:27,964
[ Gasping ]

782
00:49:41,778 --> 00:49:44,714
Everybody, listen up.

783
00:49:44,716 --> 00:49:46,816
From now on,
things are gonna be different.

784
00:49:46,818 --> 00:49:49,118
You're gonna treat me
with some goddamn respect.

785
00:49:49,120 --> 00:49:52,621
And you're not gonna
laugh at me ever again.

786
00:49:54,624 --> 00:49:56,625
None of you.

787
00:49:58,061 --> 00:50:00,596
[ Bottles Clattering ]

788
00:50:03,834 --> 00:50:06,335
- Hey, let me do that.
- Stop.

789
00:50:20,917 --> 00:50:23,986
You fucking idiot!

790
00:50:23,988 --> 00:50:28,224
I just fucking
cleaned that up!
Now look what you've done.

791
00:50:29,993 --> 00:50:33,429
[ Gasps ]
Give me some goddamn
paper towels.

792
00:50:33,431 --> 00:50:35,297
I didn't mean to
mess up.

793
00:50:35,299 --> 00:50:36,766
Yeah, but you did,
didn't you?

794
00:50:37,834 --> 00:50:39,735
Hurry up!

795
00:50:39,737 --> 00:50:41,303
Here.

796
00:50:41,305 --> 00:50:42,371
[ Dwayne ]
Do you have any tape?

797
00:50:45,742 --> 00:50:47,276
Duct tape?

798
00:50:48,512 --> 00:50:50,813
[ Kurt ]
Right over there.
By the stove. Top drawer.

799
00:50:52,916 --> 00:50:54,483
What now?

800
00:50:54,485 --> 00:50:57,119
Nothing.

801
00:50:57,121 --> 00:51:00,089
We go back to our lives
like nothing ever happened.

802
00:51:00,091 --> 00:51:04,360
You get up, you go to school,
whatever.

803
00:51:04,362 --> 00:51:06,762
Can we trust them?

804
00:51:06,764 --> 00:51:09,832
[ Scoffs ]

805
00:51:11,168 --> 00:51:13,469
[ Dwayne ]
Mica, get the shower curtain.

806
00:51:13,471 --> 00:51:16,672
[ Sniffling ]

807
00:51:19,042 --> 00:51:20,342
Give me that!

808
00:51:28,852 --> 00:51:30,719
[ Dwayne ]
Come on. Come on! Let's go!
[ Clapping ]

809
00:51:30,721 --> 00:51:32,721
Yo, get his legs.

810
00:51:36,827 --> 00:51:38,527
[ Groans ]

811
00:51:45,302 --> 00:51:46,902
- Got him?
- [ Grunts ]

812
00:51:49,172 --> 00:51:50,306
Watch it.

813
00:51:55,879 --> 00:51:58,347
<i>[ Wind Whistling ]</i>

814
00:52:04,955 --> 00:52:07,189
[ Whimpering ]

815
00:52:23,807 --> 00:52:25,207
[ Shannon Whimpering ]

816
00:52:41,458 --> 00:52:43,859
It's gonna be light soon.

817
00:52:43,861 --> 00:52:46,362
Kurt, get your car.

818
00:52:49,566 --> 00:52:51,567
Be cool, man.

819
00:52:59,176 --> 00:53:03,746
[ Panting ]

820
00:53:10,687 --> 00:53:12,955
[ Inhales ]

821
00:53:34,844 --> 00:53:37,479
[ Sobbing ]
No.

822
00:53:38,782 --> 00:53:42,251
It's okay.
It's okay, Shannon.

823
00:53:43,019 --> 00:53:45,588
[ Inhales ]
- Come on.

824
00:53:45,590 --> 00:53:48,023
[ Sniffling ]

825
00:54:28,331 --> 00:54:30,399
Kurt's right.

826
00:54:34,904 --> 00:54:36,905
Right about what?

827
00:54:41,077 --> 00:54:43,078
About me.

828
00:54:46,850 --> 00:54:48,851
I smile...

829
00:54:50,320 --> 00:54:52,621
and pretend that
everything's perfect.

830
00:54:55,525 --> 00:54:59,528
Do what's...
expected of me.

831
00:55:05,935 --> 00:55:08,003
It's all a lie.

832
00:55:13,610 --> 00:55:18,047
My life feels
like... a dream.

833
00:55:22,052 --> 00:55:26,555
So... far away
from anything real.

834
00:55:31,094 --> 00:55:32,695
[ Chuckles ]
And now this?

835
00:55:36,933 --> 00:55:39,134
I can't go back anymore.

836
00:55:41,938 --> 00:55:44,206
I can't pretend.

837
00:55:48,611 --> 00:55:52,314
We will never
go back to how we were.

838
00:55:57,187 --> 00:55:59,188
You've never
lived a lie?

839
00:56:00,423 --> 00:56:02,424
You've always been true
to yourself.

840
00:56:06,196 --> 00:56:08,197
We all lie.

841
00:56:09,999 --> 00:56:12,501
We do what we need to.

842
00:56:14,037 --> 00:56:19,541
We lie to ourselves,
choose to lie to our friends.

843
00:56:19,543 --> 00:56:22,511
Because we're not happy
with who we are.

844
00:56:23,146 --> 00:56:25,147
[ Scoffs ]

845
00:56:26,082 --> 00:56:28,117
Now we have no choice.

846
00:56:31,054 --> 00:56:34,289
It's all one big lie
that we have to live with
forever.

847
00:56:48,338 --> 00:56:53,575
[ Vehicle Approaches ]

848
00:56:53,577 --> 00:56:56,578
Mica--
The rest of you stay here.

849
00:57:22,906 --> 00:57:24,907
He's not gonna fit
inside the trunk.

850
00:57:26,242 --> 00:57:28,777
[ Sighs ]
We're gonna have to put him
in the back seat.

851
00:57:29,512 --> 00:57:30,813
Fine.
Get his legs.

852
00:57:34,717 --> 00:57:36,318
- [ Girl Screams ]
- [ Shouts ]

853
00:57:36,320 --> 00:57:39,188
- Oh, my God!
- Oh, my God!

854
00:57:39,190 --> 00:57:40,856
- Who is she?
- How do I know?

855
00:57:40,858 --> 00:57:42,124
[ Screams ]

856
00:57:42,126 --> 00:57:44,359
What have you done?

857
00:57:44,361 --> 00:57:46,428
- [ Screams ]
- Please! Please, don't.

858
00:57:46,430 --> 00:57:47,696
Stop!
Don't come any closer!

859
00:57:47,698 --> 00:57:49,965
- Just calm down.
- [ Kurt ]
Shut up! Now.

860
00:57:49,967 --> 00:57:51,033
Please.

861
00:57:51,035 --> 00:57:52,034
[ Screams ]

862
00:57:52,036 --> 00:57:53,869
What the fuck?

863
00:57:53,871 --> 00:57:55,904
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

864
00:57:55,906 --> 00:57:57,606
Look, this is no time
to panic!

865
00:57:59,375 --> 00:58:01,210
- [ Gasps ]
- Shit.

866
00:58:02,212 --> 00:58:03,479
This way.

867
00:58:03,481 --> 00:58:04,913
Stop her.

868
00:58:04,915 --> 00:58:07,115
[ Screams ]
Stop!
Everybody stop!

869
00:58:07,117 --> 00:58:08,917
Don't come any closer to me!

870
00:58:08,919 --> 00:58:10,352
We just want to talk.
It's okay.

871
00:58:10,354 --> 00:58:12,488
I saw him in there.
He's dead.

872
00:58:12,490 --> 00:58:14,790
He's fucking dead!

873
00:58:14,792 --> 00:58:16,959
Let me go!
Just let me go!

874
00:58:16,961 --> 00:58:18,961
- [ Dwayne ] Get her!
- [ Shannon ]
Wait, wait, wait, wait!

875
00:58:19,562 --> 00:58:21,129
Damn it!

876
00:58:21,131 --> 00:58:24,867
- Just go away!
Leave me alone, please!
[ Kurt ] Open the door.

877
00:58:24,869 --> 00:58:26,568
Nobody's gonna hurt you.

878
00:58:27,203 --> 00:58:28,270
Who is she?

879
00:58:28,272 --> 00:58:30,105
- Oh, my God.
Cosmo girl.
- What?

880
00:58:30,107 --> 00:58:31,673
I've seen her at school.

881
00:58:31,675 --> 00:58:33,408
[ Kim ]
What are we gonna do with her?

882
00:58:33,410 --> 00:58:34,810
[ Sobbing ]

883
00:58:46,789 --> 00:58:48,690
[ Sobs ]

884
00:58:50,226 --> 00:58:52,528
Calm down, okay?

885
00:58:53,663 --> 00:58:55,764
We just want to talk.

886
00:58:59,235 --> 00:59:02,538
Just please,
please don't hurt me.
Please.

887
00:59:04,307 --> 00:59:07,276
Please, just go away!

888
00:59:10,246 --> 00:59:13,649
No one is going to
hurt you, okay?

889
00:59:15,218 --> 00:59:17,319
I promise.

890
00:59:18,454 --> 00:59:21,123
Can you open the door?

891
00:59:21,125 --> 00:59:23,825
Just get away from me!
Just leave me alone!

892
00:59:27,864 --> 00:59:30,165
[ Gasping ]

893
00:59:30,167 --> 00:59:33,735
I saw him.
He's dead!

894
00:59:37,941 --> 00:59:40,342
I know.

895
00:59:40,344 --> 00:59:44,012
[ Girl Sobs ]
- Can you just
let us explain?

896
00:59:45,548 --> 00:59:47,549
Please.

897
00:59:48,518 --> 00:59:51,720
[ Gasping ]
[ Lacy ]
Let us in.

898
00:59:57,293 --> 00:59:59,561
[ Doorknob Rattles ]
[ Crash ]

899
01:00:03,833 --> 01:00:07,336
Stay back!
Get out!
Back up right now!

900
01:00:07,338 --> 01:00:09,504
[ Lacy ]
We just--
- Get back from me.

901
01:00:09,506 --> 01:00:12,941
We just wanna talk.
Just put it down, okay?

902
01:00:13,876 --> 01:00:16,311
No one's gonna hurt you,
I promise.

903
01:00:17,847 --> 01:00:20,916
- We just wanna talk.
- Back away from me.

904
01:00:20,918 --> 01:00:23,185
Hey,
y-you're in cheer, right?

905
01:00:24,053 --> 01:00:26,088
No, I'm in
marching band.

906
01:00:26,090 --> 01:00:28,957
- Marching band's cool.
- Shut up.

907
01:00:28,959 --> 01:00:31,059
No, it's not.

908
01:00:31,061 --> 01:00:33,795
Everybody knows
that it's not cool, okay?

909
01:00:36,065 --> 01:00:38,066
What's your name?

910
01:00:41,638 --> 01:00:43,572
Rachel.

911
01:00:44,307 --> 01:00:46,174
Rachel?

912
01:00:46,176 --> 01:00:48,443
Okay.

913
01:00:48,445 --> 01:00:53,181
Rachel, this isn't
what it appears to be.

914
01:00:55,084 --> 01:00:57,085
What is it then?

915
01:01:00,189 --> 01:01:03,358
Dylan... raped Kim.

916
01:01:05,862 --> 01:01:08,096
Dylan Hudson?

917
01:01:09,298 --> 01:01:10,999
He raped Kim?

918
01:01:14,370 --> 01:01:18,140
I don't know. It's really hard
for me to believe that
he could do anything like that.

919
01:01:18,142 --> 01:01:20,142
It's true.

920
01:01:20,144 --> 01:01:23,578
Then what happened
to Dylan?

921
01:01:23,580 --> 01:01:25,681
An accident.

922
01:01:27,083 --> 01:01:30,318
It's hard to explain,
but that is all
that you need to know.

923
01:01:32,855 --> 01:01:36,291
This is all
just really weird.

924
01:01:40,763 --> 01:01:42,964
We understand.

925
01:01:45,635 --> 01:01:47,703
Can you keep our secret?

926
01:02:00,416 --> 01:02:01,750
Okay.

927
01:02:03,820 --> 01:02:04,886
Yeah.

928
01:02:07,223 --> 01:02:10,125
[ Pole Clatters ]
- Yeah. It'll be
our little secret.

929
01:02:11,527 --> 01:02:15,330
We can, like, hang out
and do stuff together...

930
01:02:15,332 --> 01:02:18,400
Yeah, yeah.
I totally get it,
you guys.

931
01:02:18,402 --> 01:02:21,069
I'll keep it a secret.
Just us.

932
01:02:21,071 --> 01:02:24,272
That sounds great.

933
01:02:24,274 --> 01:02:29,344
Yeah.
We'll all be good friends.

934
01:02:29,346 --> 01:02:33,148
That's so great.
I have so many friends that
you guys are really gonna like.

935
01:02:34,417 --> 01:02:36,585
What is she talking about?

936
01:02:36,587 --> 01:02:40,055
Rachel,
we've got to go.

937
01:02:41,157 --> 01:02:43,792
Got it.
I'm just gonna get my shoes,
okay?

938
01:02:48,231 --> 01:02:49,297
Wait.

939
01:02:52,068 --> 01:02:54,202
Hey.

940
01:02:54,204 --> 01:02:56,638
- Do you have a car?
- Sure.

941
01:02:56,640 --> 01:02:59,174
I mean, it's my mom's.
But, yeah.

942
01:02:59,176 --> 01:03:01,042
What kind?

943
01:03:01,044 --> 01:03:03,712
An S.U.V.

944
01:03:03,714 --> 01:03:05,814
Why?

945
01:03:06,783 --> 01:03:08,984
We need a bigger car.

946
01:03:12,855 --> 01:03:15,557
Okay.
I get it.

947
01:03:17,059 --> 01:03:18,627
What are friends for?
[ Chuckles ]

948
01:03:24,033 --> 01:03:26,668
- What are you doing?
- You know
you can't trust her.

949
01:03:26,670 --> 01:03:28,236
What's with the car?

950
01:03:33,743 --> 01:03:36,878
[ Birds Cawing ]

951
01:03:55,765 --> 01:03:58,099
[ Sighs ]
I don't know about this.
Listen.

952
01:03:58,101 --> 01:04:00,669
We get Dylan in her car,
and what can she do?

953
01:04:00,671 --> 01:04:02,437
Nothing.

954
01:04:11,681 --> 01:04:15,383
- All right, now what?
- Bring your car
up the drive.

955
01:04:16,686 --> 01:04:18,687
Don't make any noise.

956
01:04:21,057 --> 01:04:23,558
Mica, go with her.

957
01:04:29,332 --> 01:04:31,099
This is insane.

958
01:04:31,101 --> 01:04:33,969
She's crazy.
We can't trust her
to keep quiet.

959
01:04:34,704 --> 01:04:37,539
Listen.
Kim's on point.

960
01:04:37,541 --> 01:04:40,809
Once we get her involved,
she won't be able to
say anything.

961
01:04:40,811 --> 01:04:42,811
[ Kim ]
Don't be stupid.

962
01:04:42,813 --> 01:04:44,913
She'll never keep
her mouth shut.

963
01:04:44,915 --> 01:04:46,481
[ Dwayne ]
I don't get it.

964
01:04:46,483 --> 01:04:50,085
This was your idea.
Get her involved?
She can't say nothing?

965
01:04:50,087 --> 01:04:51,653
And we have.

966
01:04:53,489 --> 01:04:55,790
We still won't
be able to trust her.

967
01:04:55,792 --> 01:04:59,828
We get Dylan in her car,
and we drive north. Together.

968
01:05:01,297 --> 01:05:04,466
So then
what do we do with--

969
01:05:10,773 --> 01:05:13,441
No. No.

970
01:05:13,443 --> 01:05:15,810
Do you want to
go to college?

971
01:05:16,846 --> 01:05:18,847
Or you want to go to jail?

972
01:05:20,883 --> 01:05:23,084
[ Kim ]
Don't look so surprised,
